\title{Conditional Variance}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
  The \strong{conditional variance} of a r.v. #{Y} given #{X} is defined as

  ##{
    \operatorname{Var} (Y \mid X) = E \left( (Y - E(Y \mid X))^2 \mid X \right)
  }

  this is equivalent to:

  ##{
    \operatorname{Var} (Y \mid X) = E(Y^2 \mid X) - E^2(Y \mid X)
  }
}
